text:
{
  "prompt": "A realistic 3D rendering of an electric cargo scooter named 'Chunbong Ultra'. It features a step-through tubular frame with integrated front and rear cargo racks. The front wheel is 17 inches, and the rear wheel is 15 inches with a wide on-road tire. The wheelbase is 1500mm. The scooter has a large central footboard, a mid-mounted motor, and an underfloor battery compartment. The rear features dual suspension shocks and disc brakes. The color scheme is a mix of white, black, and orange with a brown saddle. The design emphasizes balance, low center of gravity, and practical cargo delivery capabilities.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered aerodynamic version of the Chunbong ULTRA electric cargo scooter, with sleek, streamlined design enhancements for reduced air resistance. The frame remains orange tubular steel but now features a more enclosed, flowing body structure around the battery and central frame. The front includes a narrowed fork cover and integrated aerodynamic headlight cowl. Rear cargo rack is shaped with curved side panels to minimize drag. Tires remain 17-inch front and 15-inch rear. Background is clean white for clarity.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered image of the '춘봉 ULTRA' electric cargo scooter with an aerodynamic design. The scooter has a sleek black and orange body with a brown seat, front and rear 17-inch and 15-inch wheels respectively, and a long 1500mm wheelbase. Mounted on both the front and rear cargo racks are enclosed aerodynamic cylindrical storage pods (like streamlined cargo tubes), integrated smoothly into the design for reduced air drag. Set against a plain white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "This 3D-rendered image shows the Chunbong ULTRA electric scooter with an extended foot platform (50mm longer front and rear) and a redesigned seat modeled after the PCX scooter style, featuring a long, contoured, and cushioned saddle with elevated back support. The scooter includes aerodynamic black cargo pods on both front and rear racks, matte black and orange streamlined bodywork, and large wheels (17 inch front, 15 inch rear). The setting is a clean white studio background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered electric cargo scooter labeled '춘봉 ULTRA' in bold text, featuring a sleek orange and black aerodynamic frame. The scooter has a 15-liter front cargo box with a top-opening lid and a large 60-liter rear cargo container designed to fit a Papa John's family-size pizza box. The containers are smoothly integrated into the design for aerodynamic performance. It includes a comfortable PCX-style seat and extended footrests. The front wheel is 17 inches, and the rear wheel is 15 inches, both with on-road tires. The scene is set against a clean, neutral background for clarity.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered electric cargo scooter named '춘봉 ULTRA' with a sleek, aerodynamic design. It features a white and red color scheme, with a red front aerodynamic fairing and a white rear cargo section. The scooter includes a 15L front cylindrical storage box with top-opening lid, a 60L rear cargo container suitable for large pizza boxes, and a PCX-style cushioned seat. The floorboard is extended 50mm front and back, and the scooter has 17-inch front and 15-inch rear wheels with a 1500mm wheelbase. An electronically adjustable windshield is mounted above the handlebars. The frame is a tubular step-through design, combining practicality and streamlined aesthetics. Presented in a clean studio environment, side view.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A clean 3D schematic side-view illustration of a lightweight electric scooter using a dual central motor setup, designed for delivery use. The design includes two compact 500W motors mounted centrally in tandem. One motor connects to a high-ratio gearbox for low-speed torque, and the other to a low-ratio gearbox for high-speed cruising. Both motors drive a single rear wheel through a shared chain output. The image includes labeled arrows showing the motor layout, gear ratios, chain direction, and rear wheel. The scooter features a step-through frame, a 48V battery pack mounted beneath the floorboard, and front and rear cargo boxes. A minimalistic, gray-and-blue technical style background emphasizes clarity and educational value.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed mechanical diagram of a dual motor electric scooter drivetrain, with two central motors aligned in series. The first motor is connected to a high reduction gearbox for low-speed torque, and the second motor connects to a low reduction gearbox for high-speed cruising. Both motors are connected to a shared final output shaft that powers the rear wheel via a chain. The diagram is labeled and shows cutaway views of the gearboxes and internal components. Clean white background with technical blueprint style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side-view illustration showing the drive train of an electric motorcycle with a dual central motor configuration. The image highlights the swingarm, two centrally mounted motors (each with separate gear reduction), a shared output shaft, and a chain drive connecting to the rear wheel. The rear wheel includes a disc brake and sprocket. The swingarm supports the wheel and integrates cleanly with the drivetrain. The motors are compact and mounted inside the lower frame. This is a simplified engineering concept diagram on a clean white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric motorbike inspired by the BMW CE 04, designed as a high-performance delivery and commuting vehicle. The design should feature a step-through frame, extended wheelbase (around 1500mm), low and wide skateboard-style battery deck, front 17-inch wheel and rear 15-inch wide tire, dual center-mounted motors (2kW each) with separate high-torque and high-speed gearboxes. The color scheme is white with red accents, aerodynamic front fairing with electronically adjustable windshield, integrated front and rear cargo boxes, and a PCX-style comfortable seat with a rear backrest. The visual style should emphasize a mix of modern aerodynamics and robust utility, suited for urban delivery use.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
